Primitive vs Reference Types

Primitives: string, number, boolean, null, undefined, symbol, bigint

Stored directly on the stack.

Assignment creates a copy of the value.

let a = 5;
let b = a; // b gets a copy
b = 10;
console.log(a); // 5


Objects / Arrays / Functions: stored on the heap

Variables hold a reference to the heap object.

Assignment copies the reference, not the object itself.

const obj1 = { x: 1 };
const obj2 = obj1; // both point to the same object
obj2.x = 2;
console.log(obj1.x);